***********************************
**** C++ Expression Statements ****
***********************************

What makes a line of code an expression statement?
the fact it has a semicolon on the end of the expression.
Examples of expressions are:
    std::cout << "You walk into the shadowy glade. A foreboding grey stone stands before you, runes adorning it.";
    std::cout << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Suddenly the runes flash alight, a question appears. It demands your attention lest a terrible magic be unleashed upon you.";
	
	or
	
	std::cout << std::endl;
    std::cout << sum << std::endl;
    std::cout << product << std::endl;


What other lines of code are there? 

Declaration Statements - code that declares something, like a variable.

Preprocessor Directive

Main Function

Return Statements


***UNREAL ENGINE SPECIFIC***
variable names are in Pascal Case
